st Adapted Screenplay]]\n| Dee Rees and Virgil Williams\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Chicago Film Critics Association Award for Best Cinematography|Best Cinematography]]\n| Rachel Morrison\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"4\"| [[Critics' Choice Movie Awards]]\n| rowspan=\"4\"| [[23rd Critics' Choice Awards|January 11, 2018]]\n| [[Critics' Choice Movie Award for Best Supporting Actress|Best Supporting Actress]]\n| Mary J. Blige\n| {{nom}}\n| rowspan=\"4\" style=\"text-align:center;\"| <ref>{{cite news|url=http://deadline.com/2017/12/critics-choice-awards-nominations-the-shape-of-water-dunkirk-this-is-us-netflix-1202220528/|title=Critics' Choice Awards Nominations: 'The Shape Of Water' Leads With 14; Netflix Tops TV Contenders|last=Hammond|first=Pete|date=December 6, 2017|work=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|accessdate=December 7, 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Critics' Choice Movie Award for Best Acting Ensemble|Best Ensemble]]\n| The cast of ''Mudbound''\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Critics' Choice Movie Award for Best Screenplay|Best Adapted Screenplay]]\n| Dee Rees and Virgil Williams\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Critics' Choice Movie Award for Best Cinematography|Best Cinematography]]\n| Rachel Morrison\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Dallas\u2013Fort Worth Film Critics Association]]\n| [[Dallas\u2013Fort Worth Film Critics Association Awards 2017|December 13, 2017]]\n| [[Dallas\u2013Fort Worth Film Critics Association Award for Best Supporting Actress|Best Supporting Actress]]\n| Mary J. Blige\n| {{draw|3rd Place}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| <ref>{{cite web|url=http://dfwcritics.com/dfw-film-critics-name-the-shape-of-water-best-picture-of-2017/|title=DFW Film Critics Name 'The Shape of Water' Best Picture of 2017|last=Jorgenson|first=Todd|date=December 13, 2017|work=[[Dallas\u2013Fort Worth Film Critics Association]]|accessdate=December 13, 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Detroit Film Critics Society]]\n| December 7, 2017\n| Best Ensemble\n| The cast of ''Mudbound''\n| {{nom}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| <ref>{{cite news|