ing for it and aren't happy about losing their prey.\n| LineColor = 3B9DDA\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber=16\n |Title=Long Distance Calls\n | DirectedBy = Stephen Williams\n | WrittenBy = Peter David, Bill Mumy\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|1996|10|26}}\n |ShortSummary=The crew uses a powerful communications satellite to contact friends and relatives back home, but they're overheard by Reaver, a pirate who wants the satellite, and his old nemesis, Commander Goddard.\n| LineColor = 3B9DDA\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber=17\n |Title=King of the Hil\n | DirectedBy = [[David Straiton]]\n | WrittenBy = Peter David, Bill Mumy\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|1996|11|2}}\n |ShortSummary=Harlan is captured by a tribal people known as The Hil, who believe prophecy is being fulfilled.\n| LineColor = 3B9DDA\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber=18\n |Title=Truth Hurts\n | DirectedBy = [[Stephen Williams (director)]]\n | WrittenBy = Magda Liolis\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|1996|11|9}}\n |ShortSummary=Rosie can't keep secrets and, as a result, places her trust with the crew in jeopardy.\n| LineColor = 3B9DDA\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber=19\n |Title=Homeward Bound\n | DirectedBy = [[Adam Weissman]]\n | WrittenBy = Valri Bromfield\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|1996|11|16}}\n |ShortSummary=Radu receives a vision that Spung attack cruisers are coming to destroy the Christa, but he can't convince anyone that what he knows wasn't just a dream.\n| LineColor = 3B9DDA\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber=20\n |Title=All You Can Eaty\n | DirectedBy = Jeff Blyth\n | WrittenBy = [[Kevin Kopelow and Heath Seifert]]\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|1996|11|23}}\n |ShortSummary=The crew discovers a new pet, but don't realize the dangers of having it aboard the Christa.\n\n'''Guest Stars''': [[Danny Tamberelli]] as Male Prankster/Stuart, [[Michelle Trachtenberg]] as Female Prankster.\n| LineColor = 3B9DDA\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber=21\n |Title=Both Sides Now\n 