n tries them out, and the Christa becomes a runaway ship on a collision course with Radu and Bova in the shuttle.\n| LineColor = 3B9DDA\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber=25\n |Title=Trouble With Doubles\n | DirectedBy = Jeff Blyth\n | WrittenBy = Joshua Levin, Benjamin Zackheim\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|1997|1|12}}\n |ShortSummary=The crew fly by an old satellite where a Doppleganger, a creature of energy that creates evil twins of people, gets on board the ship. The evil twins begin to take over the ship.\n| LineColor = 3B9DDA\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber=26\n |Title=A Friend in Need\n | DirectedBy = Adam Weissman\n | WrittenBy = Peter David, Bill Mumy\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|1997|1|27}}\n |ShortSummary=The Space Cases check out a space station that was recently attacked by Spung.\n| LineColor = 3B9DDA\n}}\n}}\n\n== References ==\n<references />\n\n==External links==\n* {{Official website|http://www.spacecasestv.com/}}\n* {{IMDb title|0115366}}\n* {{tv.com show|space-cases}}\n\n{{Former Nickelodeon original series}}\n\n[[Category:1990s Canadian science fiction television series]]\n[[Category:1996 Canadian television series debuts]]\n[[Category:1997 Canadian television series endings]]\n[[Category:Canadian children's science fiction television series]]\n[[Category:English-language television programs]]\n[[Category:Nickelodeon shows]]\n[[Category:Space adventure television series]]\n[[Category:Television series by Cookie Jar Entertainment]]\n[[Category:Television series by DHX Media]]\n[[Category:Television series produced in Montreal]]\n[[Category:Works by Peter David]]\n", "name_user": "Ekdwc75v9Dzn91Y", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eCharacters:capitalization", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Space_Cases"}
